net.opentsdb.core

类 HistogramSpan

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.opentsdb.core.HistogramSpan
  • 所有已实现的接口:
    Iterable<HistogramDataPoint>, HistogramDataPoints

    public class HistogramSpan
extends Object
implements HistogramDataPoints
    Represents a read-only sequence of continuous histogram data points.

    This class stores a continuous sequence of HistogramRowSeqs in memory.

    从以下版本开始:
    2.4

      • getAggregatedTags

        public List<String> getAggregatedTags()
        从接口复制的说明: HistogramDataPoints
        Returns the tags associated with some but not all of the data points.

        When this instance represents the aggregation of multiple time series (same metric but different tags), HistogramDataPoints.getTags() returns the tags that are common to all data points (intersection set) whereas this method returns all the tags names that are not common to all data points (union set minus the intersection set, also called the symmetric difference).

        If this instance does not represent an aggregation of multiple time series, the list returned is empty.

        指定者:
        getAggregatedTags 在接口中 HistogramDataPoints
        返回:
        an empty list since aggregated tags cannot exist on a single span

        public int size()
        从接口复制的说明: HistogramDataPoints
        Returns the number of histogram data points.

        This method must be implemented in O(1) or O(n) where n = HistogramDataPoints.aggregatedSize() > 0.

        指定者:
        size 在接口中 HistogramDataPoints
        返回:
        the number of data points in this span, O(n) Unfortunately we must walk the entire array for every row as there may be a mix of second and millisecond timestamps

      • aggregatedSize

        public int aggregatedSize()
        从接口复制的说明: HistogramDataPoints
        Returns the number of data points aggregated in this instance.

        When this instance represents the aggregation of multiple time series (same metric but different tags), HistogramDataPoints.size() returns the number of data points after aggregation, whereas this method returns the number of data points before aggregation.

        If this instance does not represent an aggregation of multiple time series, then 0 is returned.

        指定者:
        aggregatedSize 在接口中 HistogramDataPoints
        返回:
        0 since aggregation cannot happen at the span level

      • addRow

        protected void addRow(byte[] key,
                      List<HistogramDataPoint> data_points)
        Adds a row of histogram data points to the span, merging with an existing RowSeq or creating a new one if necessary.

        Take the following rows as an example. Salt A has a row T0 at the base time T0, a row T2 at the base time T2...; Salt B has a row T1 at the base time T1, a row T3 at the base time T3... Since the salt is generated basing the following hash code: 

          
  int modulo = (new String(Arrays.copyOfRange(rowKey,  Const.SALT_WIDTH(),
  rowKey.length))).hashCode() % Const.SALT_BUCKETS();
  byte[] salt = Internal.getSalt(modulo);
        This hash scheme guarantees that all the data points with the same base time will has the same salt. 
         |---A---|       |---B---|
 |  T0   |       |   T1  |
 |-------|       |-------|
 |  T2   |       |   T3  |
 |-------|       |-------|
 |  T4   |       |   T5  |
 |-------|       |-------|
        This method expects the caller adds the rows from the same salt in the timestamp order. When the caller adds the rows from salt A, the result rows will be as below: 
         |-------|       
 |  T0   |      
 |-------|      
 |  T2   |      
 |-------|       
 |  T4   |       
 |-------|
        After the caller adds the rows from salt B, the result rows will be as below: 
         |-------|       
 |  T0   |      
 |-------|      
 |  T2   |      
 |-------|       
 |  T4   |       
 |-------|
 |  T1   |
 |-------|
 |  T3   |
 |-------|
 |  T5   |
 |-------|
        When the caller iterates the data points in the Span, the Span will firstly sort the rows. Then the final result rows will be as below: 
         |-------|       
 |  T0   |      
 |-------|      
 |  T1   |      
 |-------|       
 |  T2   |       
 |-------|
 |  T3   |
 |-------|
 |  T4   |
 |-------|
 |  T5   |
 |-------|

        参数:
        key - The row key of the row that want to add in the span
        data_points - histogram data points in the row
        抛出:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the argument and this span are for two different time series.

      • iterator

        public HistogramSeekableView iterator()
        从接口复制的说明: HistogramDataPoints
        Returns a zero-copy view to go through size() data points.

        The iterator returned must return each DataPoint in O(1). The DataPoint returned must not be stored and gets invalidated as soon as next is called on the iterator. If you want to store individual data points, you need to copy the timestamp and value out of each DataPoint into your own data structures.

        指定者:
        iterator 在接口中 Iterable<HistogramDataPoint>
        指定者:
        iterator 在接口中 HistogramDataPoints
        返回:
        an iterator to run over the list of data points

      • timestamp

        public long timestamp(int i)
        Returns the timestamp for a data point at index i if it exists. Note: To get to a timestamp this method must walk the entire byte array, i.e. O(n) so call this sparingly. Use the iterator instead.
        指定者:
        timestamp 在接口中 HistogramDataPoints
        参数:
        i - A 0 based index incremented per the number of data points in the span.
        返回:
        A Unix epoch timestamp in milliseconds
        抛出:
        IndexOutOfBoundsException - if the index would be out of bounds
